 <song> 
<title>164 ALLELUIA PERENNE</title>
<lyrics>[V1]
 164 ALLELUIA PERENNE
  SING hallelujah forth in beauteous praise,
 O citizens of heaven, and sweetly raise
 An endless hallelujah.
[V2]
 For Christ the Lord has died our souls to save; 
 We'll sing to Him, who triumphed o'er the grave, 
 An endless hallelujah.
[V3]
 His mighty love doth make our hearts rejoice, 
 And thus we render Him, with thankful voice, 
 An endless hallelujah.
[V4]
 When we have reached at length the future bliss, 
 Victorious ones, our chant shall still be this,
 An endless hallelujah.
[V5]
 Th' almighty triune God of love we'll praise, 
 And utter, in untiring, thankful lays,
 An endless hallelujah.
[V6]
 To Father, Son and Spirit we shall sing,
 Glory for evermore. To God we'll bring 
 An endless hallelujah. Amen.
</lyrics>
